, etc.).\r\n\r\nGreen-Focused Design: To prevent concrete development, extensive lawn areas, ornamental pools, and tree planting suitable for the region\'s climate have been implemented.\r\n\r\nRelaxation Areas: Shaded gazebos and benches designed for relaxation after a spa treatment are key elements of the park.\r\n\r\nIntegrated Structure with Sinek Stream\r\nThe greatest feature of this park project is its visual and physical connection with the Sinek Stream, which flows right next to it.\r\n\r\nWalking Trails: Walking paths along the stream offer thermal holidaymakers the opportunity to exercise in nature.\r\n\r\nScenic Viewpoints: There are special viewing terraces within the park from which you can observe the historical Haburman Bridge and the surrounding natural cliffs.\r\n\r\nSocial Amenities\r\nThe following areas stand out within the park where families and children can spend time:\r\n\r\nModern Children\'s Playgrounds: Safe play areas for children of families visiting the spa area.\r\n\r\nSports Equipment: Sports tracks that allow for outdoor fitness.\r\n\r\nLighting: Modern and aesthetically pleasing night lighting that keeps the spa area vibrant even in the evening hours.\r\n\r\nTip for Your Application (User Guide)\r\nYou can use the title \"Post-Spa Therapy\" when describing this park in your application.\r\n\r\nÔÇ£Walking in the park accompanied by the sound of Sinek Stream after coming out of the healing waters doubles the effect of the thermal treatment.ÔÇØ',''),(33,'S├╝t├ğ├╝ ─░mam Park─▒','ParkAndGarden','Konum ve Tarih├ğe\r\nEski Meteoroloji Alan─▒: Park, il├ğedeki eski meteoroloji istasyonunun bulundu─şu yakla┼ş─▒k 4.000 metrekarelik alan ├╝zerine in┼şa edilmi┼ştir.\r\n\r\nKarde┼şlik K├Âpr├╝s├╝: Kahramanmara┼ş ve ├çermik aras─▒ndaki karde┼şlik ba─ş─▒n─▒ simgeler; bu y├╝zden ismi Kurtulu┼ş Sava┼ş─▒ kahraman─▒ S├╝t├ğ├╝ ─░mamÔÇÖdan gelmektedir.\r\n\r\nPark─▒n ├ûne ├ç─▒kan ├ûzellikleri\r\nBu park, yap─▒ld─▒─ş─▒ d├Ânemde \"7 y─▒ld─▒zl─▒ park\" olarak nitelendirilmi┼ş ve modern peyzaj─▒yla il├ğeye yeni bir soluk getirmi┼ştir:\r\n\r\nPeyzaj ve Ye┼şil Alan: Yo─şun a─şa├ğland─▒rma ve mevsimlik ├ği├ğeklerle donat─▒lm─▒┼ş, dinlendirici bir atmosfer sunar.\r\n\r\n├çocuk ve Spor: ─░├ğerisinde standart ├ğocuk oyun gruplar─▒ ve yeti┼şkinler i├ğin a├ğ─▒k hava spor aletleri mevcuttur.\r\n\r\nOturma Alanlar─▒: Ailelerin vakit ge├ğirebilece─şi kamelyalar (pergola) ve modern oturma banklar─▒ alan─▒n her yerine yay─▒lm─▒┼şt─▒r.\r\n\r\nKullan─▒m Amac─▒\r\n├ûzellikle mahalle aralar─▒nda kalan bir park oldu─şu i├ğin yerel halk─▒n ak┼şam├╝st├╝ ├ğaylar─▒n─▒ i├ğti─şi, ├ğocuklar─▒n g├╝venle oynad─▒─ş─▒ huzurlu bir dinlenme noktas─▒ olarak bilinir.','','38.13697114904886','39.46431470457382','assets/img/places/sutcu_imam_parki.jpg','','https://s.insta360.com/p/6bada8d627807b32d5e8070b29ee52fa?region=SG','Konum ve Tarih├ğe\r\nEski Meteoroloji Alan─▒: Park, il├ğedeki eski meteoroloji istasyonunun bulundu─şu yakla┼ş─▒k 4.000 metrekarelik alan ├╝zerine in┼şa edilmi┼ştir.\r\n\r\nKarde┼şlik K├Âpr├╝s├╝: Kahramanmara┼ş ve ├çermik aras─▒ndaki karde┼şlik ba─ş─▒n─▒ simgeler; bu y├╝zden ismi Kurtulu┼ş Sava┼ş─▒ kahraman─▒ S├╝t├ğ├╝ ─░mamÔÇÖdan gelmektedir.\r\n\r\nPark─▒n ├ûne ├ç─▒kan ├ûzellikleri\r\nBu park, yap─▒ld─▒─ş─▒ d├Ânemde \"7 y─▒ld─▒zl─▒ park\" olarak nitelendirilmi┼ş ve modern peyzaj─▒yla il├ğeye yeni bir soluk getirmi┼ştir:\r\n\r\nPeyzaj ve Ye┼şil Alan: Yo─şun a─şa├ğland─▒rma ve mevsimlik ├ği├ğeklerle donat─▒lm─▒┼ş, dinlendirici bir atmosfer sunar.\r\n\r\n├çocuk ve Spor: ─░├ğerisinde standart ├ğocuk oyun gruplar─▒ ve yeti┼şkinler i├ğin a├ğ─▒k hava spor aletleri mevcuttur.\r\n\r\nOturma Alanlar─▒: Ailelerin vakit ge├ğirebilece─şi kamelyalar (pergola) ve modern oturma banklar─▒ alan─▒n her yerine yay─▒lm─▒┼şt─▒r.\r\n\r\nKullan─▒m Amac─▒\r\n├ûzellikle mahalle aralar─▒nda kalan bir park oldu─şu i├ğin yerel halk─▒n ak┼şam├╝st├╝ ├ğaylar─▒n─▒ i├ğti─şi, ├ğocuklar─▒n g├╝venle oynad─▒─ş─▒ huzurlu bir dinlenme noktas─▒ olarak bilinir.',NULL,0,'2026-02-24 10:49:40','S├╝t├ğ├╝ ─░mam Park','Location and History\r\nFormer Meteorological Station Area: The park is built on an area of ÔÇïÔÇïapproximately 4,000 square meters where the old meteorological station of the district was located.\r\n\r\nBrotherhood Bridge: Symbolizes the brotherhood between Kahramanmara┼ş and ├çermik; therefore, its name comes from S├╝t├ğ├╝ ─░mam, a hero of the War of Independence.\r\n\r\nHighlights of the Park\r\nThis park was described as a \"7-star park\" when it was built and brought a new breath to the district with its modern landscaping:\r\n\r\nLandscape and Green Areas: It offers a relaxing atmosphere with dense tree planting and seasonal flowers.\r\n\r\nChildren and Sports: It has standard children\'s play equipment and outdoor sports equipment for adults.\r\n\r\nSeating Areas: Gazebos (pergolas) and modern benches where families can spend time are spread throughout the area.\r\n\r\nPurpose of Use\r\nSince it is a park located especially in the neighborhoods, it is known as a peaceful resting place where local people drink their afternoon tea and children play safely.',''),(34,'Hanba┼ş─▒ Camii','Historical','Hanba┼ş─▒ Camii, ├çermik il├ğesinde tarih├« ├Âneme sahip cami yap─▒lar─▒ndan biridir. Geleneksel Osmanl─▒ mimarisi izlerini ta┼ş─▒yan camii, kesme ta┼ş i┼ş├ğili─şi ve ├Âzg├╝n minaresiyle dikkat ├ğekmektedir. As─▒rl─▒k tarihi boyunca il├ğe halk─▒n─▒n ibadet merkezi olan yap─▒, mimari g├╝zelli─şi ve manevi atmosferiyle ziyaret├ğilere unutulmaz bir deneyim sunmaktad─▒r.\r\n1. Tarih├ğesi ve Yap─▒l─▒┼ş─▒\r\n─░n┼şa Tarihi: Caminin k├Âkenleri olduk├ğa eskidir. Baz─▒ kaynaklar ilk in┼şas─▒n─▒ Hicri 539 (Miladi 1144) y─▒llar─▒na, Artuklu d├Ânemine kadar dayand─▒r─▒r.\r\n\r\n─░sim ├çe┼şitlili─şi: Yap─▒; Sultan Alaaddin Camii, Cami-i Atik veya banisinden dolay─▒ ┼Şah Ali Bey Camii isimleriyle de an─▒l─▒r.\r\n\r\nGeli┼şimi: Cami tek seferde yap─▒lmam─▒┼ş, zamanla eklemelerle b├╝y├╝t├╝lm├╝┼şt├╝r. Mo─şol istilas─▒ s─▒ras─▒nda zarar g├Ârm├╝┼ş, Anadolu Sel├ğuklu Sultan─▒ II. Alaeddin Keykubad d├Âneminde b├╝y├╝k bir onar─▒m g├Ârm├╝┼ş ve minaresi bu d├Ânemde eklenmi┼ştir.\r\n\r\n2. Mimari ├ûzellikleri\r\nCami, mimari a├ğ─▒dan iki farkl─▒ d├Ânemden izler ta┼ş─▒yan biti┼şik iki ana b├Âl├╝mden olu┼şur:\r\n\r\nTa├ğ Kap─▒: Do─şudaki ┼Şah Ali Bey k─▒sm─▒na ait olan ta├ğ kap─▒, Sel├ğuklu ve Artuklu ta┼ş i┼ş├ğili─şinin karakteristik ├Âzelliklerini yans─▒t─▒r. Kap─▒n─▒n ├╝zerindeki geometrik s├╝slemeler ve burmal─▒ s├╝tun├ğeler dikkat ├ğekicidir.\r\n\r\nKubbe ve ├çat─▒: Yap─▒n─▒n haremi (ana ibadet alan─▒) kare planl─▒d─▒r. ├£st ├Ârt├╝s├╝, sekizgen bir kasnak ├╝zerine oturtulmu┼ş ve kiremitle kapl─▒ bir k├╝lah ┼şeklindedir.\r\n\r\nMalzeme: D─▒┼ş duvarlarda k─▒rma ta┼ş, kap─▒ ve pencere kenarlar─▒nda ise daha ├Âzenli kesme ta┼şlar ve bazalt kullan─▒lm─▒┼şt─▒r.\r\n\r\nKapasite: Yakla┼ş─▒k 700 metrekarelik bir kullan─▒m alan─▒na sahip olan cami, ayn─▒ anda bin ki┼şiye yak─▒n cemaati a─ş─▒rlayabilmektedir.\r\n\r\n3. ├ûne ├ç─▒kan Detaylar\r\nManevi De─şeri: ─░l├ğenin en eski camisi olmas─▒ sebebiyle \"Ulu Cami\" s─▒fat─▒n─▒ ta┼ş─▒r ve ├çermikÔÇÖin manevi merkezidir.\r\n\r\nKitabeler ve Amblemler: Giri┼ş kap─▒s─▒nda bulunan ve tam olarak ├ğ├Âz├╝lememi┼ş baz─▒ amblemlerin, caminin yap─▒l─▒┼ş tarihini veya yapt─▒ran ailenin m├╝hr├╝n├╝ temsil etti─şi d├╝┼ş├╝n├╝lmektedir.\r\n\r\nKonumu: Tepe Mahallesi\'ndeki konumu nedeniyle ├ğar┼ş─▒ esnaf─▒ ve yerel halk taraf─▒ndan g├╝nl├╝k hayatta \"Hanba┼ş─▒\" mevkii ile ba─şda┼şt─▒r─▒l─▒r.','','38.13654521524159','39.45093939651319','assets/img/places/hanbasi_camii.jpg','','','',NULL,80,'2026-02-26 09:43:20','Hanba┼ş─▒ Mosque','Hanba┼ş─▒ Mosque is one of the historically significant mosque structures in ├çermik district. Bearing the traces of traditional Ottoman architecture, the mosque stands out with its cut stone workmanship and unique minaret. Serving as a center of worship for the district\'s people throughout its centuries-old history, the structure offers visitors an unforgettable experience with its architectural beauty and spiritual atmosphere.\r\n1. History and Construction\r\nConstruction Date: The mosque has very old origins. Some sources date its initial construction to the year 539 AH (1144 AD), the Artuklu period.\r\n\r\nName Variety: The structure is also known as Sultan Alaaddin Mosque, Cami-i Atik, or ┼Şah Ali Bey Mosque after its founder.\r\n\r\nDevelopment: The mosque was not built all at once; it was enlarged over time with additions. It was damaged during the Mongol invasion, underwent a major repair during the reign of the Anatolian Seljuk Sultan Alaeddin Keykubad II, and its minaret was added during this period.\r\n\r\n2. Architectural Features\r\nThe mosque consists of two main sections that bear traces of two different architectural periods:\r\n\r\nCrown Gate: The crown gate, belonging to the Shah Ali Bey section on the east, reflects the characteristic features of Seljuk and Artuklu stonework. The geometric decorations and spiral columns above the gate are noteworthy.\r\n\r\nDome and Roof: The harem (main prayer area) of the building has a square plan. Its roof is in the form of a conical roof covered with tiles, resting on an octagonal drum.\r\n\r\nMaterials: Crushed stone is used in the exterior walls, while more carefully cut stone and basalt are used around the doors and windows.\r\n\r\nCapacity: With a usable area of ÔÇïÔÇïapproximately 700 square meters, the mosque can accommodate nearly a thousand worshippers at the same time.\r\n\r\n3. Prominent Details\r\nSpiritual Value: As the oldest mosque in the district, it bears the title of \"Grand Mosque\" and is the spiritual center of ├çermik.\r\n\r\nInscriptions and Emblems: Some emblems on the entrance gate, which have not been fully deciphered, are thought to represent the date of the mosque\'s construction or the seal of the family that commissioned it.\r\n\r\nLocation: Due to its location in Tepe Mahallesi, it is associated with the \"Hanba┼ş─▒\" area in daily life by the bazaar merchants and local people.',''),(35,'F─▒rat Nehri','Nature','F─▒rat Nehri, d├╝nyan─▒n en uzun ve tarihin ak─▒┼ş─▒n─▒ ┼şekillendirmi┼ş b├╝y├╝k nehirlerinden biridir. ├çermik ├ğevresinden ge├ğen nehir; turkuaz ye┼şili sular─▒, vadileri ve ├ğevresindeki do─şal g├╝zellikleriyle foto─şraf tutkunlar─▒n─▒n ve do─şa gezginlerinin g├Âzdesidir. Sabah saatlerinde nehir k─▒y─▒s─▒nda y├╝kselen sis ve yaban hayat─▒ ile nefes kesen manzaralar─▒ ke┼şfedebilirsiniz.\r\nKarakaya K├Ây├╝ ve F─▒rat Nehri Ba─şlant─▒s─▒\r\nKarakaya K├Ây├╝, ├çermikÔÇÖin su kaynaklar─▒n─▒n F─▒rat NehriÔÇÖne yolculu─şunda stratejik bir \"bulu┼şma noktas─▒\" gibidir:\r\n\r\nSular─▒n Birle┼şme Noktas─▒: ├çermikÔÇÖin i├ğinden ge├ğen me┼şhur Sinek ├çay─▒, il├ğenin kuzeyinden do─şup g├╝neybat─▒ya do─şru ilerler. Bu ├ğay, Karakaya K├Ây├╝ÔÇÖn├╝n hemen alt─▒nda K─▒z─▒l├ğubuk ├çay─▒ ile birle┼şir.\r\n\r\nF─▒ratÔÇÖa D├Âk├╝l├╝┼ş: Bu iki g├╝├ğl├╝ ├ğay─▒n birle┼şimi, Karakaya K├Ây├╝ civar─▒ndan ge├ğerek biraz daha ileride, Konakl─▒ K├Ây├╝ ├Ân├╝nde nihayet F─▒rat NehriÔÇÖne kar─▒┼ş─▒r. Yani Karakaya, ├çermikÔÇÖin sular─▒n─▒n F─▒rat ile kucakla┼şt─▒─ş─▒ son duraklardan biridir.\r\n\r\n2. Tarihi Karakaya Han─▒ (─░pek Yolu Miras─▒)\r\nK├Ây├╝n en ├Ânemli simgelerinden biri, F─▒rat NehriÔÇÖne giden bu kadim yollar ├╝zerinde bulunan Karakaya Han─▒\'d─▒r:\r\n\r\n700 Y─▒ll─▒k Ge├ğmi┼ş: Eski ─░pek Yolu ├╝zerinde yer alan bu han─▒n yakla┼ş─▒k 700 y─▒ld─▒r ayakta oldu─şu bilinmektedir.\r\n\r\nTicaret Rotas─▒: Ge├ğmi┼şte kervanlar─▒n F─▒rat Nehri ge├ği┼şlerinden ├Ânce veya sonra konaklad─▒─ş─▒ ├Ânemli bir durak noktas─▒yd─▒. Uygulaman i├ğin bu han─▒n 360 derecelik g├Âr├╝nt├╝s├╝ harika bir i├ğerik olur.\r\n\r\n3. F─▒rat Nehri ve Karakaya Baraj─▒ Etkisi\r\nKarakaya ismi genellikle F─▒rat Nehri ├╝zerine kurulu olan Karakaya Baraj─▒ ile kar─▒┼şt─▒r─▒lsa da, asl─▒nda ikisi birbirini tamamlayan unsurlard─▒r:\r\n\r\nMikroklima Etkisi: F─▒rat Nehri ve baraj g├Âl├╝n├╝n varl─▒─ş─▒, Karakaya K├Ây├╝ ve ├ğevresinde iklimi yumu┼şat─▒r. Bu durum, b├Âlgede Diyarbak─▒r genelinden farkl─▒ olarak daha ├ğe┼şitli meyve ve sebze (nar, incir gibi) yeti┼ştirilmesine olanak sa─şlar.\r\n\r\n─░talyan K├Ây├╝ Hikayesi: Karakaya Baraj─▒ in┼şaat─▒ s─▒ras─▒nda (1976-1987) binlerce ─░talyan m├╝hendis ve i┼ş├ğinin b├Âlgede ya┼şam─▒┼ş olmas─▒, F─▒rat k─▒y─▒s─▒ndaki bu co─şrafyaya \"─░talyan K├Ây├╝\" gibi ├ğok ilgin├ğ k├╝lt├╝rel katmanlar eklemi┼ştir.\r\n\r\n4. Turistik ve Do─şal Potansiyel\r\nManzara: K├Ây├╝n y├╝ksek kesimlerinden F─▒rat NehriÔÇÖne do─şru s├╝z├╝len vadilerin manzaras─▒, do─şa foto─şraf├ğ─▒lar─▒ i├ğin e┼şsizdir.\r\n\r\nKanyon ve S─▒─ş─▒naklar: Sinek ├çay─▒ÔÇÖn─▒n F─▒ratÔÇÖa d├Âk├╝ld├╝─ş├╝ hat boyunca yer alan kayaalt─▒ s─▒─ş─▒n─▒klar─▒ ve do─şal kanyon olu┼şumlar─▒, macera turizmi i├ğin b├╝y├╝k potansiyel ta┼ş─▒r.','','38.125','39','assets/img/places/firat_nehri.jpg','','','',NULL,90,'2026-02-26 09:43:20','Euphrates','Karakaya Village and its Connection to the Euphrates River\r\nKarakaya Village is like a strategic \"meeting point\" in the journey of ├çermik\'s water resources to the Euphrates River:\r\n\r\nThe Confluence of Waters: The famous Sinek Stream, which flows through ├çermik, originates from the north of the district and flows southwest. This stream merges with the K─▒z─▒l├ğubuk Stream just below Karakaya Village.\r\n\r\nFlowing into the Euphrates: The confluence of these two powerful streams passes around Karakaya Village and, a little further on, finally joins the Euphrates River in front of Konakl─▒ Village. In other words, Karakaya is one of the last stops where ├çermik\'s waters embrace the Euphrates.\r\n\r\n2. Historic Karakaya Inn (Silk Road Heritage)\r\nOne of the most important symbols of the village is the Karakaya Inn, located on these ancient roads leading to the Euphrates River:\r\n\r\n700 Years of History: Located on the old Silk Road, this inn is known to have stood for approximately 700 years.\r\n\r\nTrade Route: In the past, it was an important stopping point where caravans stayed before or after crossing the Euphrates River. A 360-degree view of this inn would be great content for your application.\r\n\r\n3. The Effect of the Euphrates River and Karakaya Dam\r\nAlthough the name Karakaya is often confused with the Karakaya Dam built on the Euphrates River, the two are actually complementary elements:\r\n\r\nMicroclimate Effect: The presence of the Euphrates River and the dam lake moderates the climate in and around Karakaya Village. This allows for the cultivation of a wider variety of fruits and vegetables (such as pomegranates and figs) in the region, unlike the rest of Diyarbak─▒r.\r\n\r\nThe Italian Village Story: The fact that thousands of Italian engineers and workers lived in the region during the construction of the Karakaya Dam (1976-1987) added very interesting cultural layers to this geography on the banks of the Euphrates, such as the \"Italian Village\".','');
